{
  "texts": [
    "They found that sentiment analysis models outperformed bag-of-words approaches at stock, sector, and index levels, while sentiment polarity models offered limited predictive value.In terms of hybrid approaches, Srijiranon et al. [43] proposed a PCA-EMD-LSTM model that incorporates news sentiment and technical indicators to predict the next day's stock price.",
    "Their findings revealed that integrating news sentiment analysis significantly enhances the performance of LSTM-based models.",
    "Transformer-based Models in Time Series ForecastingRecent advances in stock price prediction have leveraged Transformer-based architectures and specialized time series models to improve forecasting performance.",
    "Informer [32] introduces a sparse self-attention mechanism and a generative decoder, enabling efficient long-sequence forecasting.",
    "Autoformer [44] further improves long-term prediction by incorporating a series decomposition block and an autocorrelation mechanism to capture seasonal and trend components more effectively."
  ]
}